# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the shefa-app project. This plain HTML site now includes the necessary tracking scripts to enable web analytics when deployed to Vercel.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **index.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics tracking scripts

### Implementation Details:

Added the following scripts just before the closing `</head>` tag in index.html:

```html
<!-- Vercel Web Analytics -->
<script>
    window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js"></script>
```

## Framework Detection
This is a plain HTML site (no framework like Next.js, React, etc.), so the HTML implementation approach was used as specified in the Vercel Web Analytics guide for HTML sites.

## How It Works
- The first script initializes the `window.va` function and queue for analytics
- The second script loads the Vercel analytics tracking script from `/_vercel/insights/script.js`
- The script is deferred to avoid blocking page rendering
- When deployed to Vercel with Analytics enabled, the route `/_vercel/insights/*` will be automatically created

## Next Steps
1. Deploy the app to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project â Analytics tab â Enable)
3. After deployment, verify analytics is working by checking for XHR requests to `/_vercel/insights/view` in the browser's Network tab
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab

## Notes
- No `@vercel/analytics` package installation is required for plain HTML sites
- The implementation does not include route support (this is normal for plain HTML implementations)
- The file line endings were converted from Windows (CRLF) to Unix (LF) format during the implementation
